<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1451,1983,2082]" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,463,1983,2009]" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller Argoviensis" authorityYear="1874" box="[463,725,1983,2009]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zonosperma">
<emphasis box="[463,725,1983,2009]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Euphorbia zonosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[886,954,1983,2009]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[969,1038,1983,2009]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1049,1199,1983,2009]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1252,1370,1983,2010]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
). In the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[229,342,2019,2045]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
the species occurs in open vegetation, forest edges or riversides, usually in riparian vegetation.
</paragraph>
