<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1451,157,220]" pageId="15" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,429,157,184]" pageId="15" pageNumber="208">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller Argoviensis" authorityYear="1874" box="[428,691,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zonosperma">
<emphasis box="[428,691,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="208">Euphorbia zonosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[901,1073,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophylla">
<emphasis box="[901,1073,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="208">E. heterophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but may be distinguished by the conspicuous indumentum on the cyathia and seed ornamentation (see notes under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1056,1227,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophylla">
<emphasis box="[1056,1227,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="208">E. heterophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
